<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="1709" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1709">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 850d.00/259.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Minister of Norway</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Norway</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-04">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: I have the honor to
                            acknowledge the receipt of your excellency’s note of the 1st instant
                            containing information of the appointment of Mr. W. M. Collier and
                            Minister A. G. Schmedeman as delegates to represent the Government of
                            the United States at the International Conference in relation to
                            Spitzbergen to be opened at Christiania on June 16, 1914.</p>
                        <p>I have taken pleasure in transmitting the said note to my Government.</p>
                        <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">H. Bryn</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>